      "content": "That's much better, \"thousands of participants\" definitely sounds more professional. One thing though—the editor I was talking to earlier specifically asked if we could \"specify the robustness of the study's sample size\" in the abstract. How should we word that part to make sure they feel the study is sufficiently powered and rigorous?",
